			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Arcaneus, in all honesty, I care about class balance as much as SoE seems to.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_angel.gif" alt="Angel" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I am not a developer, nor am I a mathematician.  Casting times and levels and mana costs were not put in to say that is what they should be, just to give an idea that the wouldn't be for high-end players.  Stacking issues seem wierd, but what I was thinking was that the beneficial spells would provide a lower benefit than the other classes have but when combined with our self-only or pet spells, produce effects that make us self-sufficient again.
<br />

<br />
Basically, I want magicians to have their own 'flavor' of play, and something that you start learning almost from the get go.
<br />

<br />
I feel that as magicians, we've been screwed with long enough.  We should be asking SoE for the moon by now and expect to get it.  If the magician community did in force, maybe, just maybe, Sony would give us what we want/need to bring us up in line with the other classes.  Ask for more than you need, 'settle' for what you need, and walk away a winner.
<br />

<br />
All I can say is I'm trying.<br />_________________<br />Learn as if you will Live forever.
<br />
Live as if you will Die tomorrow.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
